definition: to go out/to come out/to occur/to produce/to go beyond/to rise/to put forth/to happen/(used after a verb to indicate an outward direction or a positive result)/classifier for dramas, plays, operas etc
actually/place/classifier for houses, small buildings, institutions etc/that which/particle introducing a relative clause or passive/CL:個|个[ge4]

sentences.english: Unsurprisingly, the reaction he received from passers-by was one of complete  bewilderment.
sentences.chinese: 不出所料的是，當時與他擦身而過的人是多麼的困惑。

sentences.english: Unsurprisingly, the reaction he received from passers-by was one of complete bewilderment.
sentences.chinese: 不出所料的是，當時與他擦身而過的人是多麼的困惑。

sentences.english: True to my prediction, in the afternoon I ran to the park. There was nothing left but the tender twigs.
sentences.chinese: 果不出所料，下午再跑到公園，只剩嫩枝了。

sentences.english: Unsurprisingly, the answer turns out to be no.
sentences.chinese: 不出所料的答案是，不存在這樣的線性函數。

sentences.english: That's what I've thought, only about half of the class.
sentences.chinese: 不出所料，只有大概一半的學生看過。

sentences.english: So, as predicted, Pete went the journey.
sentences.chinese: 因此，不出所料，皮特去旅行了。

sentences.english: This was, as expected, a game with some strong challenges and lots of set-pieces.
sentences.chinese: 不出所料，這是一場對抗強悍和定位球頻現的比賽。

sentences.english: As expected, Kosovo's parliament has voted in favour of independence from Serbia.
sentences.chinese: 不出所料，科索沃的議會投票贊成脫離塞爾維亞獨立。

sentences.english: Sure enough, Tremaine lost his job.
sentences.chinese: 果然不出所料，屈裏曼丟了他的工作。

sentences.english: Well, maybe unsurprisingly, what they do is, they keep pressing the lever.
sentences.chinese: 可能不出所料地，它們會，不停地按槓桿。

sentences.english: Sure enough, the problem became very clear within minutes.
sentences.chinese: 不出所料，問題幾分鐘內就清楚了。

sentences.english: Please. So, as predicted, Pete went the journey.
sentences.chinese: 因此，不出所料，皮特去旅行了。

sentences.english: It turns out, not too surprisingly, that men really do like making more than their wives.
sentences.chinese: 結果是，不出所料，男人喜歡比妻女掙的多。

sentences.english: As expected, the corporation failed in its attempt to get an injunction preventing publication of The Stig's autobiography.
sentences.chinese: 不出所料，電視臺還是沒能阻止試替哥自傳的出版。

sentences.english: Now, not surprisingly, people who have won Olympic gold medals are very happy.
sentences.chinese: 現在，不出所料，獲金牌的人很高興。

sentences.english: Her words as expected and again the Mao surname is a cold stare.
sentences.chinese: 她的話不出所料的又得了甑氏一個白眼。

definition: to come as no surprise/as expected
lit. to follow the recipe (idiom)/fig. to follow a set pattern
to be just about to/to have just started to
due to/to stem from/to go beyond (also fig. beyond reason, expectations etc)/to go against (expectations)
